#Filter by education 

word_bank <- read.csv("vocabulary_norms_data.csv")
word_bank4 <- word_bank %>%
  filter(demo_label == "Secondary (n = 416)" | demo_label == "College (n = 870)" | demo_label == "Graduate (n = 584)")

ggplot(data = word_bank4, aes(x = age, y = vocab, group = demo_label, col = demo_label)) +
  geom_jitter(size = 0.7, alpha = 0.4) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE) +
  scale_fill_viridis_d(end = .75, option = "C") +
  scale_color_viridis_d(end = .75, option = "C", name = "Education Level") +
  labs(title = "Vocabulary Distribution by Maternal Education Level (English) ",
      x = "Age (Months)",
      y = "Vocabulary Size")  +
  theme(panel.background = element_blank(),
        #text = element_text(family = "Source Sans Pro"),
        legend.position = "top",
        legend.justification = "left")

ling_data <- read.csv("crosslinguistic_table.csv")

ling_data <- ling_data %>% 
  mutate(language = ifelse(as.character(language) == "American Sign Language", "ASL", as.character(language)))
 
ling_data2 <- ling_data %>%
  filter(uni_lemma == "dog") 


ggplot(ling_data2, aes(x = age, y = prop, color = language)) +
   geom_smooth(method = "loess", se = FALSE) +
   geom_point(size = 0.3) +
   facet_wrap(vars(language)) +
   theme_classic() +
   labs(title = "Growth Curve for a Word by Language",
        subtitle = "Word Meaning: 'Dog'",
        x = "Age (Months)",
        y = "Proportion of Children") +
   theme(legend.position = "none")
